      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="titoleto"><a name="d3e4069"> </a>Checking and adjusting timing belt tension
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4071"> </a>To check timing belt tension, use the DDS 2 instrument and the belt tensioning kit.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4073"> </a>Position the crankshaft so that the piston of the horizontal cylinder is at TDC of its power stroke with complete tool.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4075"> </a>This is achieved by aligning the timing mark (A) of the timing driveshaft pulley (1) with the reference notch (B) on the clutch
            cover (C).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_007304067.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4080"> </a>Measure the horizontal timing belt on the section (2).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4082"> </a>Before measuring the vertical timing belt, turn the crankshaft by 270° in the engine rotation direction (vertical cylinder
            TDC, in the combustion stroke), and repeat the procedure used for the horizontal cylinder, measuring the voltage on branch
            (3) of the vertical belt.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_6_007404068.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4087"> </a>D: idler tensioners
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4089"> </a>E: mobile tensioners
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4092"> </a>The tension values are those detailed in "Timing system/valves" and must be checked when the engine is cold: assembly values
            must be applied when installing a new belt, while servicing values must be applied when belt tension reaches 70 Hz.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/warning.jpg">Warning
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4095"> </a>The timing belts can become slack during normal operation. When checking belt tension, if the reading is less than 70 Hz,
         restore to the specified nominal values.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4099"> </a>If the tension value is incorrect, increase or reduce belt tension by working on screws (19) securing the mobile tensioners.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4101"> </a>Manually lift mobile tensioner (20) to tension the belt or lower it to loosen the belt.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4104"> </a>If the tension value is incorrect, increase or reduce belt tension by loosening the retaining nut (3) of mobile tensioner
            (E) and using tool no. <span class="bold">88713.3497</span> to rotate mobile tensioner (E): move mobile tensioner (E) away from the belt to loosen it or bring it nearer to tension it.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4109"> </a>Recheck the timing belt tension.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4111"> </a>Repeat the above procedure until the correct belt tension is obtained.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4113"> </a>After reaching the required tension, apply the specified grease and tighten nut (3) to a torque of 25 Nm ± 10% (min. 23 Nm
            - Max. 29 Nm).
         </div>
      </div>
